# Unity generated
[Ll]ibrary/
[Tt]emp/
[Oo]bj/
[Bb]uild/
[Bb]uilds/
[Ll]ogs/
[Uu]ser[Ss]ettings/
[Mm]emoryCaptures/

# Asset meta backups
*.private
*.private.meta

# Autogenerated VS/Rider/MD project files
.vs/
.vscode/
.idea/
ExportedObj/
*.csproj
*.unityproj
*.sln
*.suo
*.tmp
*.user
*.userprefs
*.pidb
*.booproj
*.svd
*.pdb
*.mdb
*.opendb
*.VC.db

# Unity3D generated meta files
*.pidb.meta
*.pdb.meta
*.mdb.meta

# Unity3D generated file on crash reports
sysinfo.txt

# Builds
*.apk
*.aab
*.app
*.unitypackage

# Other VCS this project also uses (Unity Version Control / Plastic)
.plastic/

# Large card-art asset library — synced via Plastic SCM cloud instead of git
/Assets/StreamingAssets/Cards/

# Sim harness build output (Tools/ is outside Assets/, so Unity's [Oo]bj/ rule above doesn't reach it)
/Tools/Sim/bin/
/Tools/Sim/obj/

# Sim self-play game dumps: 200MB+ of regenerable JSONL from a seeded, deterministic runner — the seeds
# and configs are committed, so these can be rebuilt exactly. The small .log/.csv results ARE kept: they
# are the experiment trail (win rates, CIs, ladders) and total ~0.2MB.
*.jsonl

# Public replay evidence can contain player handles and authoritative hidden-state rows. Keep the
# aggregate privacy-safe model/catalog, but never commit the regenerable raw logs.
/Tools/Sim/Results/expert-replays/raw/

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# Cloudflare wrangler local cache/account (never commit)
.wrangler/

# App secret — real value lives here on build machines only, never committed
Assets/Scripts/AppConfig.Local.cs
Assets/Scripts/AppConfig.Local.cs.meta

# Tools/Audit is a checked-in read-only analyzer; the blanket *.csproj rule above would
# silently swallow its project file and make the tool non-reproducible.
!Tools/Audit/Audit.csproj
